10/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey has been actively seeking a loan from the IMF, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said at the opening session of a conference on poverty reduction Monday (9 June). 
He said Turkey needs to continue implementing its programme with the Fund, and that conditions must be met in order to continue receiving loans. 
Erdogan announced that details of a new letter of intent to the IMF are nearly complete and that the letter itself would be submitted this weekend.
Also Monday, Erdogan met with his counterpart from Luxembourg, Jean Claude Juncker, and said relations between the two countries are strengthening day by day. 
During a meeting in Ankara, they discussed Turkey-EU relations, NATO co-operation and the Cyprus situation. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 09/06/03)
